<br>Chainsaws Were Originally Invented for Childbirth
                In the late 18th century, two Scottish doctors developed a chainsaw-like tool to assist with symphysiotomy—a surgical procedure 
                to widen the pubic cartilage to speed up difficult births before caesarean sections were common. 
                It was designed to cut through bone and cartilage efficiently.
                <br>Clouds Weigh Over a Million Pounds
                While a cumulus cloud looks fluffy and light, a 1km-sized cloud with a density of 0.5 grams per cubic meter can weigh around 500,000
                kilograms (approximately 1.1 million pounds). They stay afloat because the air below them is denser.<br>
                <br>An Octopus Has Three Hearts and Blue Blood
                Octopuses have a unique circulatory system. Two hearts work exclusively to pump blood through the gills, while a third heart
                circulates oxygenated blood to the rest of the body. Their blood is blue because it uses a copper-based protein called hemocyanin 
                o transport oxygen, rather than iron-based hemoglobin.<br>
                <br>Napoleon Was Once Attacked by Bunnies
                In 1807, after signing a peace treaty, Napoleon Bonaparte requested a rabbit hunt. His chief of staff arranged for thousands
                 (some reports say up to 3,000) of tame rabbits. When released, the rabbits—mistaking Napoleon for their handler who brought
                  food—charged him and his men instead of running away.<br>
                <br>You Cannot Hum While Holding Your Nose
                Humming requires air to pass through your nasal passages while your mouth is closed. When you seal your nose and mouth simultaneously, 
                air cannot move, making it physically impossible to produce a hum.<br>

